JOHANNESBURG - Government says there are nearly 10 million bus commuters in South Africa. It says about 300,000 Gauteng commuters use public transport buses every day.LIVE BLOG: Bus drivers down toolsThey travel on 2,500 buses provided by the Transport Department.Wednesday s bus drivers strike will be felt across the country.Affected operators include Rea Vaya Putco Autopax, Golden Arrow Gauteng Coaches Greyhound and MyCiTi.The City of Johannesburg says Metrobus drivers won t be taking part in the nationwide strike.eNCA